                    <p class="text-justify mb-3">Effective proactive maintenance requires a systematic approach. Start by creating a comprehensive checklist that covers all essential components and systems of a CCTV system. This checklist should include items such as camera functionality, lens clarity, cabling integrity, power supply stability, and video recording capabilities. Regular inspections based on this checklist will help identify any potential issues early on.</p>
                    <p class="text-justify mb-3">In addition to inspections, CCTV businesses should establish preventive maintenance schedules. These schedules should outline specific tasks and their frequency, such as camera cleaning, firmware updates, cable replacements, and equipment recalibration. By adhering to these schedules, businesses can address minor issues promptly and prevent major breakdowns.</p>

