                     <p class="text-justify mb-3">To optimize inventory management, businesses should conduct regular audits to assess the condition and quantity of spare parts. This helps identify any discrepancies, such as outdated or excess inventory, and allows for appropriate adjustments. By maintaining a well-organized and up-to-date inventory, businesses can streamline the repair process and reduce system downtime.</p>
